üß† Key Concepts
üîπ Databases

Primary databases: store raw data (GenBank, UniProtKB/TrEMBL)

Secondary databases: curated or derived (RefSeq, Pfam, InterPro)

Tertiary databases: integrative or knowledge-based (KEGG, Reactome)

üîπ Data Formats

FASTA ‚Äî sequence data

GenBank ‚Äî annotated nucleotide records

GFF / BED ‚Äî genome feature annotations

XML / JSON ‚Äî structured data for web and APIs

üß¨ NCBI E-utilities Cheatsheet
Tool	Description	Example Command
esearch	Search a database	esearch -db nucleotide -query "BRCA1[Gene]"
efetch	Retrieve records in a given format	efetch -db nucleotide -id NM_007294 -format fasta
esummary	Get metadata summary	`esearch -db protein -query insulin
elink	Find linked data between databases	elink -dbfrom gene -db protein -id 672
xtract	Extract specific fields	`efetch -db gene -id 672 -format xml
entrez-direct install	Setup	conda install -c bioconda entrez-direct
üîß EMBOSS Tools
Tool	Purpose	Example
seqret	Convert file formats	seqret -sequence seq.gb -outseq seq.fasta
transeq	Translate nucleotide to protein	transeq dna.fasta prot.fasta
patmatmotifs	Search for motifs via PROSITE	patmatmotifs protein.fasta motifs.txt
needle / water	Pairwise sequence alignment	needle seq1.fasta seq2.fasta
getorf	Find open reading frames	getorf genome.fasta orfs.fasta
